HELLO UNIVERSE


This is a python script to create graph_sheets of any size. 
(I can't remember the exact word but it is same as cartesian grids we used in highschool math plotting)

====================================
usage: generate_graph.py [-h] [--width WIDTH] [--height HEIGHT] [--sections SECTIONS] [--subsections SUBSECTIONS] [--padding PADDING]
                         [--tag TAG]

Generate graph paper.

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --width WIDTH         Width of the page in pixels, DefaultVaule: 1024
  --height HEIGHT       height of the page in pixels, DefaultVaule: 1024
  --sections SECTIONS   number of section, the width should be divided, DefaultVaule: 10
  --subsections SUBSECTIONS
                        number of subsections each section should be divided, DefaultVaule: 10
  --padding PADDING     outer margins width in pixels for the graph, , DefaultVaule: 12
  --tag TAG             suffix for output file name, DefaultVaule: default
========================================

refer images in ./output directory for reference.

I am developer and use these images as backgroud reference for my designs (i.e., to figure out padding, etc on go)

hope this will help.



